parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The EPS warning light illuminates
the power steering assist cuts out
the steering wheel becomes hard to maneuver
the vehicle drifts or becomes unresponsive
the radio and interior lights may flash on and off
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power steering can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering assist cuts out intermittently
the steering wheel becomes hard to maneuver
the EPS warning light may illuminate
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The EPS warning light illuminates
the power steering assist cuts out
the steering wheel becomes hard to maneuver
the vehicle drifts or becomes unresponsive
and the radio and interior lights may flash on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle can cause the vehicle to lose propulsion, leading to a loss of control, especially when accelerating from a stop or driving on a busy highway. This can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Loud bang or clunking noise
vehicle will not move forward or in reverse
vehicle rolls backward or loses propulsion
grinding or buzzing sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the vibration damper can lead to front axle failure, causing the vehicle to lose propulsion and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion under the vibration damper
reduced axle diameter
weakening of the axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission fluid pressure switch can cause the vehicle to lurch or hesitate, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Lurching or hesitation while driving
MIL indicator light comes on
transmission fluid pressure switch error code.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unstable steering can cause the vehicle to veer out of its lane, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Intermittent veering of the vehicle
loss of steering feedback
rapid and extreme corrections required to maintain control.
